SAP SuccessFactors Work Zone Empowering the Intelligent Enterprise and Total Workforce Management  Publish Date: April 2023 If you have any questions, comments or suggestions please contact:  Kris Schratz kris.schratz@sap.com     Icon for customer story  Icon for demo tip  Icon for competitive differentiator  Icon for powerful question  Icon calling out analyst award 

Background of this Demo Story: SAP SuccessFactors Work Zone provides an intuitive digital workplace experience that provides easy access to relevant business applications and processes, information, and communication in a unified entry point for work - with the worker at the center. It empowers teams and departments to effectively communicate and engage with workers without requiring IT infrastructure or support and extends across the entire organization to streamline processes with customizable, guided experiences that integrate with disparate systems to present a simple and easy experience for the employee.  Workers can also create communities where they can share knowledge and experiences with rich multimedia and micro-learning capabilities, helping to enrich critical programs such as onboarding and training and development.  Prerequisites:  1. For this demo, you will need to reserve the BRE0T01 demo landscape using the Shared Instance Reservation system. 2. Before each demo: To be sure that SSO to Fieldglass works properly during the demo, log in as Nolan Waters (nwaters), and click on the External Worker tile.  This will open Fieldglass in a separate tab that you can then close.  SSO is not yet set up for the external worker so will need to login prior to the demo to enable the link in Work Zone to work.  3. Optional: For better performance, cache the projects screens prior to the demo.    Solutions Included in the Story: - SAP SuccessFactors Work Zone - SAP SuccessFactors - SAP S/4 HANA Cloud - Fieldglass - Concur - Ariba - Qualtrics  Demo System(s) Required:  For this demo, you will need to reserve the BRE0T01 demo landscape using the Shared Instance Reservation system.  Tips and Tricks:  1. As you go through the demo, please know that there is a mix of standard and custom functionality in the demo system.  However, there is no functionality that a customer would not be able to build on their own.  (Please see the Appendix at the end of this script for a list of the delivered content.) Each customer will have different requirements so this is just one example of how a customer might configure SAP SuccessFactors Work Zone. 2. You will see that not all the widgets displayed on a page are functional.  It is highly recommended that you do a thorough run-through of this demo to familiarize yourself with how everything works so you are better prepared for the live demo to your customer. 3. Because this is a shared demo environment, it is highly recommended that you run through the demo quickly right before your customer demo to make sure that no changes have been made to the content and that everything works as expected.  There are instructions in the Appendix portion of the demo on how to add back in any missing content. 4. Please do not make any changes to the workspaces or demo content.  This is an integrated demo environment shared with others so any changes you make will impact others. 5. This demo is designed to be modular and the demo flow should be personalized for your customer.  You can go deeper into solution areas that are more relevant to the customer and skip those solutions that your customer may not be interested in. 6. Please know that the SSO for Ariba and Concur is “sticky”.  While the demo script only shows one user accessing both of these solutions, if you go “off script” and want to access Ariba or Concur as the other user, you will need to logout of these apps individually.  7. You will need to open sessions in separate browsers in order for the Fieldglass logins for the manager and external worker to work correctly.  If you are using Chrome in Incognito mode, make sure that the slider for “Block Third Party Cookies” is in the off position when you open the session for nwaters.  Otherwise, the TWM dashboard may not render correctly. 8. For the SAC tenant, you must perform a one-time action Activating your SAP ID# on the SAC Planning Public Authentication Landscape. Please follow the directions in this Blog Post:  https://jam4.sapjam.com/blogs/show/j4mjNiDhJX8gdTKtyjZ2oN . 9. For Task Center, if you are going to show Open Task in Concur, you must log into Work Zone as nwaters before your demo and click on the External Worker tile on My Workspace to activate SSO.  
Overall Story Message:  SAP SuccessFactors Work Zone empowers the intelligent enterprise by connecting experiences across multiple solutions, the SAP and SuccessFactors landscape as well as 3rd party applications and brings it into one, intuitive place to help employee’s get their work done.  SAP SuccessFactors Work Zone provides a personalized, intuitive digital workplace experience that provides easy access to relevant business applications and processes, information, and communication in a unified entry point for work – with the worker at the center.   By intelligently surfacing the most relevant data, content, recommendations, insights and actions to an individual, work just got simpler.  Demo Flow Demo Story/Message: Demo Intro  Presenter – Introduction to Story  The way people work is changing. In todays’ current environment, many people are working and collaborating remotely for the first time.  In addition, their working hours have shifted from a “normal” workday to a more flexible workday that balances work with other responsibilities like caring for an aging parent or young children. Because of this, ensuring workers- both employees and external workers – are engaged is even more challenging.  Engaged employees are 40% less likely to turn over, 12 times more likely to be brand advocates, and potentially deliver three times more revenue as their less-engaged colleagues. (Source)  
  In addition, the modern workforce itself has fundamentally changed.  Whether driven by the challenges of the pandemic or just general, run-of-the-mill need for change – employees are restless. We’ve all seen the media coverage.  § Microsoft work trend index shows that 40% of people want to change jobs this year (Microsoft WorkLab Blog via Fast Company). § A survey found 38% of workers are planning to leave their current job over the next few months vs 26% in US (Personio Report via TechRepublic). Organizations are seeing the benefits of tapping into an external workforce. On average, external workers can represent up to 42% of the workforce (Oxford Research). And companies increasing reliance on this external workforce. And this increased reliance will necessitate the need to ensure that all workers – internal and external – are able to collaborate and work together to achieve the organization’s goals and business objectives.  Organizations will need to provide their people managers with the tools and information they need to effectively manage their total workforce and need to provide an engaging worker experience for all. 

 The people that make up your entire workforce-–from FTEs to contingent to services providers—have increasingly high expectations about the quality, consistency and depth of engagement and experience they have with your organization. According to Josh Bersin, employee experience isn’t just about providing a consumer-grade experience with HR technology. It’s also about ensuring that employees feel connected to their work as well as their colleagues, understand their organization’s strategy and mission and how they support it, and can easily find the information they need for tasks like requesting time off, identifying development opportunities, and accessing the various disparate systems they may need to get their work done. HR can help lead the organization to implement new ways of supporting employees, boosting productivity, and creating a more agile, flexible and engaged workforce. Connecting the people and talent strategy to the overall objectives of the organization is vital for the company’s success and aligning everyone to the organization‘s purpose. Aligning financial and human resources data helps measure the impact of HR on the business or the ROI of people spend. Yet, it transcends the entire organization since HR initiatives and data are needed across the whole enterprise and all lines of business.  Unfortunately, organizations have disconnected systems, and there is no single access point to manage the total workforce. This results in a lack of visibility and often confusion. If departments operate in silos, companies cannot match their people strategy to the demands of the business and this adds unnecessary complexity to their work experience. 
 SuccessFactors Work Zone enables organizations to provide workers – ALL workers – with an intuitive, personalized digital workplace that’s centered on optimizing the employee experience. Employees are empowered to be productive anywhere, thanks to convenient access to relevant business applications and processes, information, learning, and more.  SuccessFactors Work Zone also centralizes employee communications and provides collaboration capabilities, helping ensure people are informed, connected, and focused on what matters most. With Work Zone, FTEs and your External Workforce:  • Access the tools they need to work from any device • See intelligence-driven, employee-relevant recommendations, insights, and actions • Get guided experiences that are cross-departmental and help simplify tasks Persona: Nolan Waters, Project Mgr Demo Mode: Laptop Location: Home Office Vignette 1 –  Project Planning Nolan reviews and plans his current projects.

 Nolan Waters is responsible for the delivery and management of many large projects at his organization.  Like many workers today, Nolan is working remotely for the first time in his career.  He’s just sat down at his desk to begin his day and has logged into the system. Nolan’s day always begins here.  Immediately upon logging into his digital workplace, he can see the latest company news.  For instance, he can see that the company’s 2021 strategy plan has been published and where to get more information.  He doesn’t have to go searching for it – everything is right here front and center.   Everything on this home page is configurable based upon your company’s requirements.  In this example, Nolan can see more content that his organization is promoting like company events, blogs posts, and HR announcements.   While SAP SuccessFactors Work Zone enables communication across the organization, the information on this page – including the company feed – is personalized so Nolan only sees content that is applicable to his role.  This eliminates “information overload” by presenting a unified feed of information that is relevant and personalized to him. The main home screen also provides context-aware areas that are based on his role within the organization. All this content helps Nolan to feel connected to the rest of the organization which is especially important when so many employees are working remotely.   Organizations can also get a quick pulse on how their employees are doing by including a quick one-question survey on how they’re feeling.  These quick assessments using SAP Qualtrics can be leveraged on most pages to gain insight and understand how employees are feeling.  This enables organizations to deliver better and more personalized experiences that increase employee satisfaction and engagement. • Click on the “More” tab then click on the Learning tab 
 Organizations can set up additional pages that help employees get to relevant content quickly.  For instance, we see pages for additional HR content as well as a Learning page. His organization has built a culture of learning because it recognizes that many employees value the opportunity for development and career advancement.  To encourage employees to access learning, they’ve created a learning page within Work Zone for HR.  Here we see that Nolan can quickly search for courses or content and can even access relevant third-party content like TedTalks right from here. • Click on the My Workspace tab SAP SuccessFactors Work Zone empowers the intelligent enterprise by connecting experiences across the SAP landscape

By intelligently surfacing the most relevant data, content, recommendations, insights and actions to an individual, work becomes much simpler, more productive, and more enjoyable.  Speed to get these positions filled is the top priority, so Nolan takes a look at Time to Hire to see what he might expect when trying to staff. On average, he should expect about 5 days to fill this position with an external worker, while he may wait about 40 days if he wants to hire someone full time.  Nolan knows speed typically comes at a cost, and he does have a budget to track.  • From the Dashboard drop down, select Rates – High & Low   
 As he compares costs across the workforce, he sees that Machine Learning Engineers and Cyber Security Analysts are two of the most expensive roles to fill, as he expected. If we break down the average hourly cost and compare external workers to FTE cost, he’s finding that external workers could be up to $20/hour more.  That cost certainly adds up, but Nolan knows he only needs these resources for a short time. And speed is the most important factor right now. Nolan would like to do a quick internal search first to see if he’s lucky enough to find internal resources, with the appropriate skill sets, who are available immediately. That would save him the cost while getting someone onboard quickly. If not, he knows that hiring an external worker for a temporary period is the way to go. • Learning Approvals  
 As new internal and external resources onboard a new project, it is only logical that they gain access to update their product knowledge. One of Nolan’s many responsibilities is to make sure that his team continues to develop and grow. He notices that some requests for learning need his approval and he takes care of them on the spot, to ensure business continuity and compliance. He doesn’t have to leave his workspace. With a single click he can approve his employees’ registration to classes and courses, both internal and external.

 Summary  
  
 You saw today how SAP SuccessFactors Work Zone provides an intuitive digital workplace experience that provides unified and easy access to relevant business applications and processes, information, and collaboration – with the worker at the center.    SAP SuccessFactors Work Zone intelligently surfaces the most relevant data, content, recommendations, insights, and actions to an individual, making work simpler. And you saw how it goes a step further to “hyper-personalize” so not only do workers get the information most relevant to them but they can configure their workspace to their own preferences and job responsibilities with the apps and page layout they need in order to do their work.   Every task that Nolan Waters, our Projects Delivery Director, Gwen Steward, our Senior Consultant, and Jeffrey Simpson, our external worker, performed began and ended with SAP SuccessFactors Work Zone.  Whether accessing project details, searching for talent, hiring a contingent worker, approving expenses, accessing a project workspace, shopping for team gifts, or awarding a spot bonus for a job well done, you saw how SAP SuccessFactors Work Zone for HR truly enables the intelligent enterprise and Total Workforce Management by connecting experiences across the SAP landscape and third-party applications and bringing it into one, unified place to help workers get their work done through a positive and engaging experience for employees, managers, and external workers.   Only SAP delivers an intelligent solution that streamlines engagement, communication, and collaboration, and enables true Total Workforce Management.
